<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Iljin, Acta Inst. Bot. Ac. Sc. USSR, ser. 1, 2: 124" authorityYear="1936" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex pamirica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pamirica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Atriplex pamirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a morphologically highly recognisable species (
<bibRefCitation author="Sukhorukov, AP" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" refId="B101" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, 2006. Zur Systematik und Chorologie der in Russland und den benachbarten Staaten (in den Grenzen der ehemaligen USSR) vorkommenden Atriplex-Arten (Chenopodiaceae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 108 B: 307-420." title="Zur Systematik und Chorologie der in Russland und den benachbarten Staaten (in den Grenzen der ehemaligen USSR) vorkommenden Atriplex-Arten (Chenopodiaceae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien 108 B: 307 - 420." year="2006">Sukhorukov 2006</bibRefCitation>
). The varietal rank 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex tatarica var. pamirica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="tatarica" variety="pamirica">Atriplex tatarica var. pamirica</taxonomicName>
, proposed by Chu in Kung and Tsien (1979), cannot be accepted. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Atriplex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Atriplex tatarica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tatarica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Atriplex tatarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a taller plant with an aphyllous or bracteose inflorescence. The results of molecular phylogeny have confirmed the specific rank of 
<taxonomicName family="Chenopodiacea" genus="A." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. pamirica" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="pamirica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">A. pamirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.1000169" author="Kadereit, G" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" pagination="1664 - 1687" refId="B56" refString="Kadereit, G, Zacharias, E, Mavrodiev, E, Sukhorukov, AP, 2010. Molecular phylogeny of Atripliceae (Chenopodioideae, Chenopodiaceae): Implications for systematics, biogeography, flower and fruit evolution, and the origin of C4 photosynthesis. American Journal of Botany 97 (10): 1664 - 1687, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.1000169" title="Molecular phylogeny of Atripliceae (Chenopodioideae, Chenopodiaceae): Implications for systematics, biogeography, flower and fruit evolution, and the origin of C 4 photosynthesis." url="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.1000169" volume="97" year="2010">Kadereit et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<pageBreakToken pageId="41" pageNumber="42" start="start">Description</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Annual up to 30(50) cm, branched at the base with ascending stems but not forming tumble-weed habit at the fruiting stage. Stems and leaves covered with white and brown bladder hairs. Leaves grey on both sides, oblong or spatulate, entire or crisp. Inflorescence leafy. Bract-like cover enclosing the female flowers 3.0-7.0 mm long, rhombic, entire or dentate with concrescent (up to 1/3-1/2) valves, valves sessile or pedicellate (pedicels up to 3 mm), sclerified and inflated in the lower part, abaxial surface smooth or with two small outgrowths. Seeds heteromorphic: red seeds convex, 1.0-1.7 mm, brown seeds flattened, 1.2-1.8 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Screes or roadsides at altitudes of 3500-5300 m a.s.l.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Flowering: July-September; fruiting: September-October.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
